[The actual Seminole County Health Alert can be read at
<http://images.ibsys.com/2001/0216/464208.jpg> - Mod.MPP]
[It is surprising the official alert did not include vaccinating horses.
Horses may acquire rabies through inadvertent contact with wild animals.
Horses come into contact with so many people by nature of their companion
animal status. Horses should have been included in this alert. - Mod. TG]
